# whisper-agent-sandbox runtime configuration.
#
# This file is read by the systemd unit (whisper-agent-sandbox.service)
# as an EnvironmentFile and is marked as a config backup in the package
# manifest, so pacman will preserve local edits across upgrades.

# Listen address. Default is the IPv6 wildcard, which on Linux accepts
# both IPv6 and IPv4 (via v4-mapped) without extra configuration — a
# remote whisper-agent server can connect from either family.
#
# Override to 127.0.0.1:9810 for loopback-only deployments where the
# whisper-agent server runs on the same host.
WHISPER_AGENT_SANDBOX_LISTEN=[::]:9810
